Shooting Stars Football Club of Ibadan are set to complete the signing of experienced goalkeeper Okemute Odah from Al Ain FC DAILY POST can exclusively report. A reliable source close to the team disclosed to DAILY POST that the former Lobi Stars goalie is currently in Ibadan to finalize the deal. “One of the big-name players in Shooting Stars camp is Okemute Odah. He is currently in Ibadan,” the source told DAILY POST. Odah is an experienced goalkeeper, who had stints with the likes of Warri Wolves, Lobi Stars and Rivers United before moving to Saudi Arabia. The shot-stopper has also represented Nigeria at the youth level. He was part of Nigeria’s home-based squad that took part in the 2016 African Nations Championship in Rwanda.